# Core Services And Data

Follow the existing core architecture before adding or changing service, repository, controller, wrapper, or model behavior.

## Interfaces And Implementations

- Every service, wrapper, controller, or repository implementation should have a matching interface when that pattern exists locally.
- Interface files use `i_<name>.dart` or `i_<name>_service.dart` according to the nearby folder.
- Services, wrappers, and controllers use `interfaces/` and `implementations/`.
- Repositories currently use `interfaces/` and `implementation/`; follow the existing local folder name.
- Register injectable dependencies consistently with existing core registration patterns.

## Results And Errors

- Preserve existing result/error types and propagation patterns.
- Do not expose internal service details directly to UI.
- Handle external service failures at the layer where similar failures are already handled.
- Avoid changing public interfaces unless the issue or feature requires it and the user confirms.

## Models And Mapping

- Keep DTOs, database models, API models, enums, and mappers in `packages/models`.
- Use existing mapper patterns instead of ad hoc conversions.
- Do not duplicate shared model shapes in app code.
- Regenerate generated model files through Melos/build_runner.

## Tests

- Add focused tests for business logic, error handling, and mapping behavior.
- Use existing mocks from `mocks.dart` before adding new mock specs.
